[[File:Волк 3.jpg|150 px]]
|  | Kerr 1792&lt;ref&gt;{{ITIS|id=726809 |taxon=''Canis lupus albus'' Kerr, 1792}}&lt;/ref&gt;
|  | A large subspecies, with adults measuring 112–137&amp;nbsp;cm, and weighing 36.6–52&amp;nbsp;kg. The fur is very long, dense, fluffy and soft and is usually very light and grey in colour. The lower fur is lead-grey and the upper fur is reddish-grey.&lt;ref name=&quot;soviet&quot; /&gt;
|  | Northern [[tundra]] and [[forest]] zones in the European and Asian parts of [[Russia]] and [[Kamchatka]]. Outside Russia, its range includes the extreme north of [[Scandinavia]]&lt;ref name=&quot;soviet&quot; /&gt;
|  | ''dybowskii'' (Domaniewski, 1926), ''kamtschaticus'' (Dybowski, 1922),
''turuchanensis'' (Ognev, 1923)&lt;ref&gt;{{MSW3 Wozencraft | pages = | id =14000740 }}&lt;/ref&gt;
|- style=&quot;vertical-align: top;&quot;
| style=&quot;font-style: italic;&quot; | [[extinction|†]]''' Kenai Peninsula wolf'''&lt;/br&gt;[[Canis lupus alces]]
|  | Goldman 1941&lt;ref&gt;{{ITIS|id=726810 |taxon=''Canis lupus alces'' Goldman, 1941}}&lt;/ref&gt;
|  | A large wolf measuring over 180&amp;nbsp;cm in length and weighing 45–63&amp;nbsp;kg. It is thought that its large size was an adaptation to hunting the extremely large moose of the [[Kenai Peninsula]].&lt;ref name=&quot;day&quot; /&gt;
|  | [[Kenai Peninsula]]
|  | 
|- style=&quot;vertical-align: top;&quot;
| style=&quot;font-style: italic;&quot; | '''Arabian wolf'''&lt;/br&gt;[[Arabian wolf|Canis lupus arabs]]
[[Image:Canis lupus arabic.JPG|150 px]]
|  | Pocock 1934&lt;ref&gt;{{ITIS|id=726811 |taxon=''Canis lupus arabs'' Pocock, 1934}}&lt;/ref&gt;
|  | A small, &quot;desert adapted&quot; wolf that is around 66&amp;nbsp;cm tall and weighs, on average, about 18&amp;nbsp;kg.&lt;ref name=&quot;Lopez&quot; /&gt; Its fur coat varies from short in the summer and long in the winter, possibly because of solar radiation.&lt;ref name=&quot;Paquet&quot;&gt;{{cite book | author = Fred H. Harrington, [[Paul C. Paquet]] | title = Wolves of the World: Perspectives of Behavior, Ecology, and Conservation | year = 1982 | isbn = 0815509057 | page = 474}}&lt;/ref&gt;
|  | Southern [[Israel]], Southern and western [[Iraq]], [[Oman]], [[Yemen]], [[Jordan]], [[Saudi Arabia]], and probably some parts of the [[Sinai Peninsula]]
|  | 
|- style=&quot;vertical-align: top;&quot;
| style=&quot;font-style: italic;&quot; | '''Arctic wolf'''&lt;/br&gt;[[Arctic wolf|Canis lupus arctos]]
[[File:Canis lupus arctos qtl1.jpg|150 px]]
|  | Pocock 1935&lt;ref&gt;{{ITIS|id=726812 |taxon=''Canis lupus arctos'' Pocock, 1935}}&lt;/ref&gt;
|  | A medium sized wolf that is between 64 and 79&amp;nbsp;cm tall and 89 to 189&amp;nbsp;cm long, weighing between 35 and 45&amp;nbsp;kg on average, though there have been specimens found weighing up to 68&amp;nbsp;kg.&lt;ref&gt;[http://wwf.panda.org/about_our_earth/species/profiles/mammals/arcticwolf/ &quot;White wolf of the North&quot;], [[World Wide Fund for Nature]]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.torontozoo.com/ExploretheZoo/AnimalDetails.asp?AnimalId=403 &quot;Arctic wolf&quot;], [[Toronto Zoo]]&lt;/ref&gt;
|  | [[Northern Canada|Canadian Arctic]], [[Alaska]] and northern [[Greenland]]
|  | 
|- style=&quot;vertical-align: top;&quot;
| style=&quot;font-style: italic;&quot; | '''Mexican wolf'''&lt;/br&gt;[[Mexican wolf|Canis lupus baileyi]]
[[File:Mexican Wolf 065.jpg|150 px]]
|  | Nelson and Goldman 1929&lt;ref&gt;{{ITIS|id=726813 |taxon=''Canis lupus baileyi'' Nelson and Goldman, 1929}}&lt;/ref&gt;
|  | A small subspecies which weighs 25–45&amp;nbsp;kg and measures 140–170&amp;nbsp;cm in total length (nose to tip of tail), and 72–80&amp;nbsp;cm in shoulder height. The pelt contains a mix of gray, black, brown, and rust colors in a characteristic pattern, with white underparts&lt;ref name=&quot;green&quot;&gt;[http://www.eebweb.arizona.edu/Courses/Ecol406R_506R/Parsons1998-MexWolf.pdf ''&quot;Green Fire&quot; Returns to the Southwest: Reintroduction of the Mexican Wolf'']-
Author(s): David R. Parsons. Source: Wildlife Society Bulletin, Vol. 26, No. 4, Commemorative Issue Celebrating the 50th Anniversary of ''&quot;A Sand County Almanac&quot;'' and the Legacy of Aldo Leopold (Winter, 1998), pp. 799-807. Published by: Allen Press&lt;/ref&gt;
|  | Northern [[Mexico]], western [[Texas]], southern [[New Mexico]], and southeastern and central [[Arizona]]&lt;ref name=&quot;green&quot; /&gt;
|  | 
