|  | G. M. Allen and Barbour 1937
|  | A white coloured subspecies typically measuring 180&amp;nbsp;cm in length and weighing 45&amp;nbsp;kg&lt;ref name=&quot;day&quot;&gt;''The Encyclopedia of Vanished Species'' by David Day, Universe Books ltd. 1981. ISBN 0947889302&lt;/ref&gt;
