| style=&quot;font-style: italic;&quot; | [[extinction|†]] '''Bernard's wolf'''&lt;/br&gt;[[Bernard's Wolf|Canis lupus bernardi]]
|  | Anderson 1943
|  | This subspecies became extinct in 1934, though it was described as &quot;white with black-tipped hair along the ridge of the back&quot;.&lt;ref&gt;[http://books.google.com/books?id=I-kSmWLc6vYC&amp;pg=PA40&amp;lpg=PA40&amp;dq=%22Bernard%27s+Wolf%22&amp;source=bl&amp;ots=WondBDY25l&amp;sig=Md1LSHTckWuxTFfUGIR6h_94sfc&amp;hl=en&amp;ei=wetRTIHOH4GknQf4iOCPBA&amp;sa=X&amp;oi=book_result&amp;ct=result&amp;resnum=7&amp;ved=0CCMQ6AEwBjgK#v=onepage&amp;q=%22Bernard's%20Wolf%22&amp;f=false &quot;Bernard, P. and J.&quot;], ''The Eponym Dictionary of Mammals'' by Bo Beolens, Michael Watkins and Michael Grayson, JHU Press, 2009, Pg. 40&lt;/ref&gt;
|  | Limited to [[Banks Island|Banks]] and [[Victoria Island]]s in the arctic
|  | ''banksianus'' (Anderson, 1943)&lt;ref&gt;{{MSW3 Wozencraft | pages = | id =14000746 }}&lt;/ref&gt;
|- style=&quot;vertical-align: top;&quot;
| style=&quot;font-style: italic;&quot; | '''Steppe wolf'''&lt;/br&gt;[[Canis lupus campestris]]
|  | Dwigubski 1804
|  | A wolf of average size with short, coarse and sparse fur. The fur is light grey on the sides and rusty, brownish grey on the back&lt;ref name=&quot;soviet&quot; /&gt;
|  | Northern [[Ukraine]], southern [[Kazakhstan]], [[Caucasus]] and Trans-Caucasus&lt;ref name=&quot;soviet&quot; /&gt;
|  | ''bactrianus'' (Laptev, 1929), ''cubanenesis'' (Ognev, 1923), ''desertorum'' (Bogdanov, 1882)&lt;ref&gt;{{MSW3 Wozencraft | pages = | id =14000747 }}&lt;/ref&gt;
