| style=&quot;font-style: italic;&quot; | '''Tibetan wolf'''&lt;/br&gt;[[Tibetan Wolf|Canis lupus chanco]]
[[File:Canis lupus chanco1.jpg|150 px]]
|  | Gray 1863
|  | A small subspecies rarely exceeding 45&amp;nbsp;kg in weight. It is of a light, whitish-grey colour, with an admixture of brownish tones on the upper part of the body&lt;ref name=&quot;soviet&quot; /&gt;
|  | [[Central Asia]] from [[Turkestan]], [[Tien Shan]] throughout [[Tibet]] to [[Mongolia]], Northern [[China]], [[Shensi]], [[Sichuan]], [[Yunnan]], the Western [[Himalayas]] in [[Kashmir]] from [[Chitral]] to [[Lahul]].&lt;ref name=&quot;pocock&quot;&gt;[http://ia341313.us.archive.org/0/items/PocockMammalia2/pocock2.pdf ''Fauna of British India: Mammals Volume 2'' by R. I. Pocock, printed by Taylor and Francis, 1941]&lt;/ref&gt; Also occurs in the [[Korean peninsula]]&lt;ref name=&quot;AINU&quot;&gt;{{cite book | author = Walker, Brett L. | title = The Lost Wolves Of Japan | year = 2005 | isbn = 0295984929 | page = 331}}&lt;/ref&gt;
|  | ''coreanus'' (Abe, 1923), ''dorogostaiskii'' (Skalon, 1936), ''ekloni'' ([[Nikolai Przewalski|Przewalski]], 1883), ''filchneri'' ([[Paul Matschie|Matschie]], 1907), ''karanorensis'' (Matschie, 1907), ''laniger'' ([[Brian Houghton Hodgson|Hodgson]], 1847), ''niger'' ([[Philip Sclater|Sclater]], 1874), ''tschiliensis'' (Matschie, 1907)&lt;ref&gt;{{MSW3 Wozencraft | pages = | id =14000748 }}&lt;/ref&gt;
