      <text xml:space="preserve">{{Infobox Roman emperor
| name            =Constantius II
|full name =Flavius Julius Constantius (from birth to accession);&lt;/br&gt; Flavius Julius Constantius Caesar (as Caesar);&lt;/br&gt; Flavius Julius Constantius Augustus (as Augustus)
|title=[[Roman emperor|Emperor]] of the [[Roman Empire]]
| image           =[[File:Bust of Constantius II (Mary Harrsch).jpg|250px]]
| caption         =Bust of Constantius II
| reign           = '''324''' (November 13) – '''337''' (May 22): [[Caesar (title)#Tetrarchy|Caesar]] under his father, [[Constantine I]] &lt;br&gt; '''337 – 340''': co-[[Augustus (honorific)|Augustus]] (ruled Asian provinces &amp; [[History of Roman Egypt|Egypt]]) with [[Constantine II (emperor)|Constantine II]] and [[Constans]] &lt;br&gt; '''340 – 350''': co-[[Augustus (honorific)|Augustus]] (ruled Asian provinces &amp; [[History of Roman Egypt|Egypt]]) with [[Constans]] &lt;br&gt; '''350''' – '''361''' (November 3): Sole [[Augustus (honorific)|Augustus]] of the Roman Empire
